HEADWORD: Chrysoberyl
<hw>Chrys"o*ber`yl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>chrysoberyllus</ets>, Gr. <?/; <grk>chryso`s</grk> gold + <?/
beryl.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral, found in crystals, of a
yellow to green or brown color, and consisting of aluminia and glucina.
It is very hard, and is often used as a gem.</def>⟦br⟧
